                <h1>Cleveland: A Journey Through History</h1>
                <p>Cleveland, founded in 1796 near the mouth of the Cuyahoga River, emerged as a vital trade center due to its strategic location. The city played a significant role during the Industrial Revolution, becoming a hub for manufacturing, transportation, and immigration. Its rich heritage is showcased through landmarks, arts, and diverse cultures that continue to thrive today.</p>
